The following C++ code fragment shows the class definition of an ADT hash table that stores student information. In this implementation, the chaining approach is adopted to resolve collisions.

class ChainStudentNode
{
private:
    int studentID; // the ID (key) of a student
    string name;   // the name of a student
    string dept;   // the department name of a student
    ChainStudentNode *next;
    friend class StudentHashTable;
}; // end ChainStudentNode

class StudentHashTable
{
public:
    void insertStudent (int sID, string sName, string sDept);
    string retrieveName (int sID);
